This paper discusses building an embedded inference engine using deep learning frameworks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also discusses the use of ARM Compute Library (ACL), which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and embedded systems (cs.EM). Finally, the paper mentions the potential applications of the inference engine in augmented reality (cs.AR).
